{
  "doc_id": "28574",
  "text": "Among the 11 lung specific genes, CHIL4 (Chitinase-like protein 4), LYZ1 (lysozyme) and SEMA3G (semaphorin 3G) belong to category i. CHIL4 is a member of the Chitinase-like proteins, which are indicators of inflammation and cancer in humans [CITATION_1] . CHIL4 itself is also suggested to play an important role in airway inflammation [CITATION_2] . LYZ1 is the primary antibacterial component secreted by submucosal glands in tracheobronchial airways in lung [CITATION_3] .",
